msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../O/oriental-food.rst:9
msgid ""
"Hackers display an intense tropism towards oriental cuisine, especially "
"Chinese, and especially of the spicier varieties such as Szechuan and Hunan."
" This phenomenon (which has also been observed in subcultures that overlap "
"heavily with hackerdom, most notably science-fiction fandom) has never been "
"satisfactorily explained, but is sufficiently intense that one can assume "
"the target of a hackish dinner expedition to be the best local Chinese place"
" and be right at least three times out of four. See also :ref:`ravs`\\, "
":ref:`great-wall`\\, :ref:`stir-fried-random`\\, :ref:`laser-chicken`\\, "
":ref:`Yu-Shiang-Whole-Fish`\\. Thai, Indian, Korean, Burmese, and Vietnamese"
" cuisines are also quite popular."
msgstr ""
"ハッカーは東洋料理、とりわけ中華料理、なかでも四川や湖南のようなより辛い種類に対して強烈な走性を示す。この現象(ハッカー界と大きく重なる下位文化、最も顕著にはSFファンダムでも観察されている)は満足に説明されたことがないが、十分に強烈であるため、ハッカーの夕食遠征の目的地は地元で最高の中華料理店だと想定すれば、少なくとも四回に三回は当たると言ってよい。\\"
" :ref:`ravs`\\ 、\\ :ref:`great-wall`\\ 、\\ :ref:`stir-fried-random`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`laser-chicken`\\ 、\\ :ref:`Yu-Shiang-Whole-Fish`\\ "
"も参照。タイ、インド、韓国、ビルマ、ベトナムの料理もかなり人気がある。"
